><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Or worse, the uberguilds are simply turning the plat into Real World Cash via playerauctions<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
VI really made this easier with the addition of $tormhammer. It's easy to take a twink over with a pile of things like Elemental Bows (200k a shot?), sell them for several million pp, and quickly convert the PP into $$ with playerauctions.<br>
<br>
This is a much more common occurance than people are willing to admit, and quite a few uberguilds look the other way about it because it'd be impossible for some of those members doing it to keep playing EQ without the influx of cash funds. If your choice is to have a top cleric quit because of the inability to pay for his apartment anymore, or to look the other way when he farms elemental tradeskill shit to sell on PA ... most people look the other way.<br>
<br>
And - 15 million PP is quite a low ball guess. If I had to guess the PP value of droppables in my guild now (elemental tradeskill gear, mostly) it would be well over 50 million pp, or more. The simply staggering amount of pp that items like Earthweave/Waterweave and other elemental armor itself gets it amazing, let alone the truly valuable items like bows and stuff. Not to mention that it takes 2 groups to gank Tormax now, or 3 to do AOW and those items still sell for 100k+ (helm, BoC, WD Helm, etc). Or Zlandicar (COM), etc. There's so much high end droppable gear now that a virtual economy was just to certain to grow up. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;font-family:courier;font-size:small;">&quot;It never stops hurting, you just go faster...&quot;</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> - <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-family:courier;font-size:small;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Greg LeMond</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kadathdreamfire>Kadath Dreamfire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1058<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/28/03 4:30:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26200.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://zorak.monmouth.edu/~posten/minigang.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Runes - Finding and Buying</span><hr size=1> For reference, I have never seen a rune of glint for sale.<br>
